'''Boonkua Lourvanij''' (9 August 1930 &ndash; 7 April 2015)<ref>{{cite web|title=งานสวดพระอภิธรรมศพ คุณบุญเกื้อ เหล่าวานิช (16-22 เมษายน 2558)|work=Skeet & Trap Shooting Association of Thailand website|url=http://www.thaiclayshooting.com/th/stat-news/186--16-22-2558|accessdate=3 January 2016}}{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> was a Thai businessman and [[Shooting sport|sports shooter]]. He competed at the [[1968 Summer Olympics]] and the [[1972 Summer Olympics]],<ref name="SportsRef">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/lo/boonkua-lourvanij-1.html |title=Boonkua Lourvanij |accessdate=1 January 2016 |work=Sports Reference |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305142032/https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/lo/boonkua-lourvanij-1.html |archivedate=5 March 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> was a founding member of the Skeet & Trap Shooting Association of Thailand, and founded and served as CEO of the Asoke Motors Company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thaiclayshooting.com/th/about-us/history|title=ประวัติสมาคมยิงเป้าบินแห่งประเทศไทย|work=Skeet & Trap Shooting Association of Thailand website|accessdate=1 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=อโศกทาวเวอร์นำความฝันสู่ความสำเร็จ|magazine=Manager|date=July 1984|url=http://info.gotomanager.com/news/details.aspx?id=9131|accessdate=3 January 2016|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304075815/http://info.gotomanager.com/news/details.aspx?id=9131|archivedate=4 March 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
