{{Infobox company | name = Cativa Natureza | logo = Cativanatureza.gif | foundation = 2008 | founder = Rose Bezecry | location_city = [[Curitiba]] | location_country = Brazil | key_people = | industry = Personal care | products = Cosmetics | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | num_employees = | parent = | subsid = | homepage = [http://www.cativanatureza.com.br/?idioma=en Cativa Natureza] | intl = }}
'''CativaNatureza''', a company from Paraná, Brazil, is pointed out as a reference in the Brazilian Market of traceable cosmetics made of organic raw materials by the international press specialized in the area<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.organic-market.info/web/Fairs_+_Conferences/BioFach_Globally/Brazil:_dynamic_growth_of_the_domestic_market_and_exports/214/322/0/17015|title = Brazil: dynamic growth of the domestic market and exports|date = 02/07/2014|accessdate = 2014-07-19|author = |publisher =Organic-Market }}</ref> Besides being recognized by experts in the global market as one of the key-participants of the Brazilian organic industry. The organic sector, to which the company belongs to, is considered by specialists to be in full expansion in the country (data of July 2014).<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.organic-market.info/web/Organic_Retail_Trade/General/Brazil:_organic_as_profiling_tool/207/210/0/17051.html|title = Organic as Profiling Tool|date = 01/07/2014|accessdate= 2014-07-14|author = |publisher = Organic Market}}</ref>
==History== Cativa Natureza is Brazil’s first chain of stores to sell cosmetics made of traceable organic raw materials. Founded in the beginning of 2008, by Rose Bezecry, in the Municipal Market of [[Curitiba]] – [[Paraná (state)|Paraná]] the Ecologic Capital, the company may be considered one of the first Brazilian brands in the sector of organic products in the country- Cativa Natureza holds a strong relationship of respect for [[Ecologically sustainable development|ecological sustainable development]] and strives for [[recycling]] issues and the certification of all its selling products. Nowadays (data July 2014), the chain has ten stores distributed throughout the Brazil. Cativa Natureza is considered one of the most innovative entreprises in the branch because of its unusual concoctions and the unique ingredients used in its formulations - for instance [[yerba mate]] mulateiro extract and [[coriander]] oil.
==Awards== The company was awarded in 2010 by IBDN<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.ibdn.org.br/novo/index.php/eventos/conferencias/curitiba/cur2010.html|title = Prêmio Mérito Ambiental 2010 (original im Portuguese)|date = 12/05/2010|accessdate = 2014-07-13|author = |publisher =Instituto Brasileiro de Defesa da Natureza }}</ref> (Brazilian Institute of Nature's Preservation) for being the first retail chain of [[Product certification|certified organic cosmetics]] in Brazil.
